# MCAT Prep - Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Local-first: all practice, analytics, and exam flows must work offline via RxDB (Dexie/IndexedDB).
- Cloud is optional: Supabase sync only when authenticated and online.
- Feature-driven layout under `src/features/{dashboard,exam-emulator,flashcards,compliance}`.
- Shared UI atoms in `src/components`.

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode; no `any` without justification.
- React function components + hooks; prefer colocated feature modules.
- Tailwind for styling; Pearson VUE exam UI uses fixed layout tokens in `exam-emulator/styles.ts`.

## Performance
- Local AI runs in a Web Worker; never block the main thread during inference.
- Target 60 FPS during WebGPU model execution.

## Compliance ("Guarantee Mode")
- Incorrect answers trigger modal blockade when mode is active.
- `infoGap`, `distractorTrap`, `preventiveRule` must be non-empty before continue.
- Persist to `question_logs.mistakeAnalysis` with `complianceLogged: true`.

## FSRS
- Interval: I(s, r) = s * ln(r) / ln(0.9), default r = 0.9.
- Overdue flashcards > 200 blocks new practice passage routing.

## Testing
- Vitest for unit/integration tests; verify offline persistence and FSRS math.
